This is definitely a really weird one. The Level 9 monster that we are looking at today is XX-Saber Gottoms who is a Level 9 EARTH Beast-Warrior Synchro Monster that requires a Tuner monster and 1 or more monsters as Synchro Material. Gottoms does not need any non-Tuners to actual Synchro Summon him, but it is not like really matters in the context of this Deck. His effect is that you can Tribute an X-Saber monster to discard a random card from your opponent's hand. We can surprisingly use this effect to a very large degree, but I will get to that in just a bit. I wanted to try to actually use X-Sabers in this Deck that is focused on Summoning XX-Saber Gottoms. I have like 5 Prediction Princess Decks that all make use of the Red Resonator Predaplant engine from my Ib Ham Prediction Princess Deck on the backburner that will be posted soon, but I just want to steer clear of utilizing that engine for a bit. But to be fair, with what X-Saber has currently without any new support, they do a decent job of getting to Gottoms and your Prediction Princess combos. We are focusing on using the effect of Rescue Cat in order to get to XX-Saber Darksoul and X-Saber Airbellum, just like how you would back when X-Saber was running around. Except Rescue Cat has an errata now which doesn't really matter much as we just need the Level 3 Tuner and non-Tuner bodies. I will be describing a 2.5-card combo, a 3.5-card combo, and a 4.5-card combo for the Deck. They are just reiterating on each other based on the inclusion of an additional specific card in your opening hand. You may not get to them per say, but it is good to know these combos to potentially pull them off. Our 2.5-card combo begins with Summoner Monk, XX-Saber Faultroll, and a Spell to discard. Normal Summon Summoner Monk who goes to Defense on Summon. Activate its effect discarding a Spell to Special Summon Rescue Cat from Deck. Send Rescue Cat to GY to Special Summon XX-Saber Darksoul and X-Saber Airbellum from Deck. Now that you control 2 X-Sabers, Special Summon Faultroll from hand. Synchro Airbellum and Summoner Monk into Shooting Riser Dragon. Shooting Riser sends Shaddoll Beast from Deck to GY to reduce its Level from 7 to 2. Synchro the Level 2 Shooting Riser and Darksoul into Ib the World Chalicer Justiciar who adds World Legacy Monstrosity to hand on Synchro Summon. Use Faultroll's effect to Special Summon back Airbellum from GY. Synchro Airbellum and Faultroll into XX-Saber Gottoms. Activate Monstrosity targeting Gottoms and Special Summon Gizmek Kaku, the Supreme Shining Sky Stag and Thunder King, the Lightning Strike Kaiju from Deck. Overlay for Mereologic Aggregator and yada yada. I mean the combo works, but I just wish that we could do more. And that’s where the 3.5-card combo comes into play. This is if you draw Gottoms' Second Call in addition to your 2.5-card combo. Gottoms’ Second Call is a Spell Card that lets you target and Special Summon 2 X-Saber monsters from your GY ignoring their Summoning Conditions, changing their ATk to 0, and destroying them during the End Phase. If we open it in addition to our 2.5-card combo, we could use it alongside XX-Saber Gottoms to loop 4 cards out of our opponent's hand. Second Call brings back Faultroll and Airbellum/Darksoul, Tribute Airbellum/Darksoul (whichever you brought back) with Gottoms to discard a card from your opponent's hand, Special Summon that monster back with Faultroll, Tribute that monster again to discard another card, and then Tribute Faultroll for the 3rd discard. Then, if we already activated Monstrosity targeting Gottoms, we can Tribute Gottoms for the 4th card ripped out of your opponent’s hand. But what about that 4.5-card combo? That is if you draw World Legacy Monstrosity or World Legacy Succession in your opening hand. Ib searches whichever you did not open. In that case, after you made Aggregator to send Herald of the Arc Light for a Ritual search, reattach Herald to Aggregator, and Link off Aggregator for Gravity Controller to get another search with Herald, you can use Succession to bring back Gottoms from GY to Linkpoint. Then, you can Tribute Gottoms for the 5th card ripped out of your opponent’s hand. Am I telling you that you should be handripping your opponent in this X-Saber Prediction Princess Deck? I’m not telling you that you should be focused on doing it, but if you do draw Gottoms’ second call, you will be able to gain a lot of advantage over your opponent with said handrips, so if you are able to do it in whatever situation you find yourself in, you should do it.

For the Main Deck monsters: 3 Prediction Princess Traotrei, 1 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, and 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. Tarotrei can Quick Effect flip a monster on field face-up or face-down and during your End Phase, she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-down. Tarotreith must either be Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei’s End Phase effect. Her Flip Effect Special Summons a Flip Monster from your Deck face-down and she can also Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back from the GY face-down if she is Tributed and sent there. Her Flip Effect adds a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from your Deck to your hand and while she is face-up on the field, your Ritual Monsters gain targeting and destruction protection from your opponent’s effects. 1 Deus-X Krawler which negates all activated monster effects on your opponent’s side of the field after it has been flipped face-up and if it is destroyed on field, you can search for a Level 9 monster with a different Type and Attribute than it. 1 Gizmek Kaku, the Supreme Shining Sky Stag and 1 Thunder King, the Lightningstrike Kaiju as our Level 9 Monstrosity targets in Deck. 3 Summoner Monk which discards a Spell to Special Summon a Level 4 monster from Deck. 3 Rescue Cat which sends itself from field to GY to Special Summon 2 Level 3 or lower Beast monsters from Deck with their effects negated and destroying them during the End Phase. 1 Shaddoll Beast as a Level 5 monster to send off of Shooting Riser Dragon to make it a Level 2. Beast also doubles as a Flip Monster which is also nice. For the X-Saber monsters: 3 XX-Saber Faultroll, 1 XX-Saber Darksoul, and 1 X-Saber Airbellum. I might seem crazy playing only 1 Airbellum and Darksoul for Rescue Cat, but playing 2 copies of each doubles the chances of you actually drawing it, so my ingenious biology major brain tells me to play just the single copy of each and just not draw them. It's that easy. Faultroll cannot be Normal Summoned/Set and must be Special Summoned from hand by controlling 2 or more face-up X-Saber monsters and cannot be Special Summoned by other ways. And as a soft once per turn, he can Special Summon a Level 4 or lower X-Saber monster from your GY. No clue why he has this Summoning Condition/Restriction, but it isn’t too bad of a downside. Faultroll is still a very good X-Saber card. Darksoul has an effect that activates during the End Phase which adds an X-Saber monster from Deck to hand if it was sent from your field to the GY this turn. I mean, sure. I guess we could get another Faultroll for next turn, if we can actually summon it next turn. Airbellum’s effect really does not matter as we are just using it as a Level 3 Tuner monster.

For the Spell/Traps: 3 Pot of Prosperity. 1 Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 3 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which Ritual Summons a Prediction Princess Ritual Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down and you can banish it from the GY during the Standby Phase to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess monster from your Deck face-down. 2 Prediction Ritual which only RItual Summons Prediction Princess Tarotrei and you can banish it from GY except the turn it was sent there to search for a Prediction Princess Ritual Monster. 3 Pre-Preparation of Rites. Not only can this get you to Tarotrei and Prediction Ritual, you can also discard Prediction Ritual for Summoner Monk if you want since you are getting more Ritual Spells off of Mereologic Aggregator. 3 World Legacy Monstrosity which either Special Summons a Level 9 monster from hand or targets a Level 9 monster you control to Special Summon 2 Level 9 monsters from your Deck with a different Type and Attribute but with different names. We are playing 3 because we can only get to Ib if we draw Summoner Monk, but if we draw Cat and Faultroll, we can still get to Gottoms and have a good chance of opening Monstrosity to get 2 additional Level 9’s onto the field. 1 World Legacy Succession which Special Summons back a monster from GY to Linkpoint. And 2 Gottoms’ Second Call for the handripping shenanigans I described earlier. We are not focusing on it, so we don’t really have to play 3, and besides, drawing 2 of them in your opener kind of hurts when you can’t do anything with them.

Extra Deck: 1 Master of Ham which Special Summons a Flip Monster from hand or Deck face-down on Fusion Summon. 1 Ravenous Crocodragon Archethys and 1 Cloudcastle as alternative Level 9 Synchro options that actually allow Monstrosity to get Bibliomuse from Deck when targeting them. 1 XX-Saber Gottoms. 1 Shooting Riser Dragon which is a Level 7 Synchro Tuner that can modulate its Level. 1 Ib the World Chalice Justiciar which searches for a World Legacy card on Synchro Summon. 2 Herald of the Arc Light which searches for a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell if sent to GY. 2 Mereologic Aggregator. 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 S:P Little Knight, 1 I:P Masquerena, and 1 Gravity Controller. 

Side Deck: 3 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 2 Thunder King, the Lightningstrike Kaiju, 1 Kurikara Divincarnate, 3 Dark Ruler No More, 1 Harpie’s Feather Duster, 2 Lightning Storm, and 3 Evenly Matched.

deck_excerpt: A Diabellstar Rescue-ACE deck made for a serious reason.
deck_description:
On January 1st of 2024, a massive earthquake with a magnitude of 7.6 hit central Japan, killing 92 people, injuring at least 300 people, and leaving thousands of people sleeping in evacuation shelters. Japanese rescuers are moving heaven and Earth to find survivors. And as someone who loves Japan, I felt the need to make this tribute deck, named "Rescue-ACE Victory" because I truly believe that the people of Japan--the victims and their families especially--can bounce back from this tragedy.

 

This Rescue-ACE deck uses the new Snake-Eyes support from Phantom Nightmare, namely Populus and Sinful Spoils of Evil - Silvera.. The point of this deck is still to go first and have Turbulence set 4 of your cards. So it's either go first or burst.

deck_excerpt: Number 43 FTK ft. Survival Instinct + Rebirth Judgment
deck_description:
Hi! Here, the objective is to FTK the opponent with "Number 43" thanks to Type adjustments coming from "Rebirth Judgment", where "Survival Instinct" also plays key role. Let's get into action!

 

 

Gameplan

1) Link Summon Saryuja when you have exactly 4 cards in Main Deck. Activate Saryuja to shuffle 3 cards and choose Traps as first two choices to ensure you will always draw them, which also matters for "The Dark Magicians" (TDM).

2) Place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon with its ability to unlock "Primal Seed" loop.

3) Special Summon "Fusion Parasite" with Saryuja, which lets you Fusion Summon TDM by using Parasite + Spellcaster as materials. Activate TDM to draw your first Trap and enable it. To reset TDM for another time, send it to GY with "Self-Mummification" and revive with "Monster Reborn" afterwards.

4) If you have XYZ Summoned Number 13 and sent it to GY, you can revive it with "Monster Reborn". Then, overlay into Number 43 with "Rank-Up-Magic Launch" and send to GY with "Self-Mummification". Do it another time for 2nd copy of Number 43 and revive both Number 43 monsters with "Monster Reborn".

5) Send all monsters from your hand to GY with "Contract with the Void". Then, deliver all monsters but Chaos Emperor + 2 x Number 43 to GY with "Self-Mummification", if any.

6) What you did in #5 was more fuel for "Survival Instict". After activating "Rebirth Judgment" and choosing Type as Dinosaur, you can follow it up with "Survival Instict". Banish all of your monsters in GY to gain lots of LP. With both Number 43 monsters present, they will convert life into death for your opponent.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Rebirth Judgment" can be collected by purchasing "Vortex of Magic" deck. 30 UR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "The Dark Magicians" can be collected by purchasing "Cybernetic Successor" deck. 30 UR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Monster Reborn" is given for free, if you have completed the tutorial to save 30 UR!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Moray of Avarice" can be found within "Treasures of the Cosmic Ocean" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Primal Seed" + "Pot of Acquistiveness" + "Ravenous" + "Fusion Parasite" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 90 SR and 60 UR!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 510 SR and 210 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. If you have any questions, feel free to ask. Have fun in Master Duel!

deck_excerpt: Slifer, Face Cards, OTK, Draw Power, Advantage
deck_description:
Man I feel like playing Egyptian Gods today and Slifer has always been my favourite but what should I do? All support is written for The Winged Dragon of Ra only, so I'm out of luck I guess... 

STOP at once! You may not know about it but the Three Musketeers of Face Cards are what supports Slifer nowadays and it actually works well! Today we take a look at how to play a pure Face Card Slifer Variant in all of it's Detail, let's start: 

 

How do I play Poker in Yugioh?

The Musketeers are based on Poker Cards and they can easily get 3 Monsters onto the field to summon 1 of 4 Boss Monsters. There's a 5th one in form of Royal Straight Slasher too which we don't use in this Deck (way to convoluted).  That card is best used in a Variant which doesn't play Slifer at all since he needs a lot of additional setup to get maximum value. 

With that out of the way you have to understand that all this Deck wants to do is to summon 2 to 3 Monsters and use these for their Boss Monster plays. The little Extra on top is their Card Advantage. They have a Monster a Spell and a Trap that each return the Musketeers back to the Deck and themselves back to the Hand to be used without limit. Combine that with the additional Draw Power and a 10000 ATK Slifer the Sky Dragon is a real possibility within this Deck. Now that's exciting right? 

Now this may all sound quite Confusing and that's why I'm gonna Explain this Deck in more Detail below now: 

 

Who are the three Musketeers anyway? 

To answer that it's King's Knight , Queen's Knight and Jack's Knight. 2 Normal Monsters and one effect Monster. So what do we do with these three Musketeers?  

You wanna summon the L4 Queen's Knight first, most of the time. To do that use the Spell Joker's Straight who setups all 3 Knights at once or you use the Monster Joker's Knight to mill the Queen from the Deck and Copy her name with Joker. In followup turns the Trap Joker's Wild and the Permanent Trap Court of Cards are just a few of many cards who can setup the initial Queen onto the field once more to start again. 

After that it's time for the L4 King's Knight to enter the field who on Normal Summon special summons the L5 Jack's Knight from the Deck onto the field but only if you already control Queen's Knight. And with that you already control all 3 which turns your Deck fully online. 

If you use Imperial Bower and Joker's Knight you summon Bower first to get any 2 Musketeers onto the field and after that you mill the missing name with Joker's Knight to get all 3 names active like that. 

Or you use Imperial Bower first and then Joker's Straight to have 5 Monsters on the field. Like that you can also go into various Extra Deck plays or end on multiple Arcana Boss Monsters in one turn. 

Until now everything is still pretty simple right? Get 3 Monsters on the field = Profit. Well now it's time to look at the rest of the Deck and see how it all works together. 

 

I didn't open any of my Starters do I surrender? 

No no no don't loose hope just yet and start reading your other cards. This Deck is not as one sided as one may think at first glance. We didn't draw Joker's Straight , Joker's Knight or Imperial Bower but that doesn't mean we should Klick the surrender Button. 

The 3rd Joker card Joker's Wild is a great normal Trap which can copy the effects of your 4 in Archetype Spell Cards which we all play. Use the Trap in the opponents turn to copy Joker's Straight and follow up with a set Thunderspeed Summon to get an easy Slifer the Sky Dragon interruption during the opponents turn. Remember that Joker's Straight allows you to normal summon any Monster from your Hand not just King's Knight. 

Thunderspeed Summon which I just mentioned is a quick play that enables a L10 Tribute summon and if the three Musketeers are active you can search Slifer the Sky Dragon or Arcana Triumph Joker first and then summon them. A great card all around for a surprise big chonky dragon or girl. Yes this card also searches The Winged Dragon of Ra but this god has more then enough support within it's own Archetype already. 

You can also use Court of Cards to get a Musketeer from Hand or GY onto the field every turn. You can even banish the Musketeers from the Hand or GY to Draw 1 to 3 Cards. Only one effect may be used per turn but since it's a permanent Trap you can use it every turn. This card is one of the pillars which makes Slifer in this Deck that much more Formidable. 

Face Card Fusion is a normal Spell which can summon a Light Warrior Fusion which we have 2 different ones by using Material in the Hand or Field. If you control a Musketeer doesn't matter how many you can use a Monster from the Deck as Material too. This card is an easy route into Idaten the Conqueror Star who may then search Joker's Knight to setup a Link-3 Arcana Extra Joker. More on this Link target and the other Fusion target we have a little later. 

Royal Straight is yet another quick play which can send Musketeers from Hand or Field to the GY to summon Arcana Triumph Joker , Arcana Extra Joker or Arcana Knight Joker from Hand, Deck, Extra Deck or GY. This card can be quite devastating but also has some setup to it which holds it's potential back. If you play Royal Straight Slasher and intend to summon him you need this card but for our sake it's an one of option with Joker's Wild available whenever we need it. 

The Revived Sky God is the Slifer Trap which specials him back from the GY in defense position and lets each player draw until they have 6 cards in Hand. This can't be negated or interrupted at all. You can then Banish this card from the GY later to get a Monster Reborn from the Deck or GY on top of the Deck and Draw 1 card if Slifer is in the GY (Which he will be since if he's special summoned he's send to the GY during the End Phase). 

 

The Joker has a Ace in his Sleeve

All three Joker cards which are Joker's Knight , Joker's Straight and Joker's Wild have an additional GY effect. During each End Phase if they are in the GY you can shuffle a LIGHT Warrior from the GY back into the Deck to add that card back to your Hand. 

Not only does this recycle your Full Combo Setup every turn it also generates further Hand advantage for Slifer and since it's a Monster, Spell and Trap which all come back to the Hand your Arcana Boss Monsters gain profit from it as well. You are not even limited to the Musketeers only, so feel free to Recycle your out of Archetype options too, even so most of the time you will recycle the Musketeers. 

 

Arcana and Egyptian Forces united!

It's Boss Monster time. Like mentioned earlier this Deck has 4 Boss Monsters. Let's see what the whole payoff for this Strategy is at the end of the day: 

Arcana Extra Joker is a Link-3 Warrior with 2800 ATK who needs 3 Monsters with different Names as Material. It's Link arrows are upper center and lower left and right. If he or a Monster he points to is targeted by an effect you can discard the same Type of card (Monster, Spell, Trap) of the activated Card to negate that activation. This is a soft once per turn so multiple copies of this card can use this effect multiple times. You can even use this effect to prevent targeting on an opponents Monster like Equip Spells if he's pointing to that Monster. 

If this Link summoned card is destroyed by Battle you can special a Queen's Knight from Deck (Or any other L4 Normal Monster) and add a L4 Warrior from the Deck to your Hand. With that you can search King's Knight who may then fulfill his Condition to summon Jack's Knight.

Technically with the Joker cards combined you can Loop this card every turn if the opponent has a stronger Monster to run into but there may be an even stronger option for you to summon instead of just him. He's the upgraded form of King's Knight in terms of lore. 

 

Arcana Knight Joker is a L9 Warrior Fusion Monsters which needs the three Musketeers as Material. His Statline is a menacing 3800/2500. As a soft once per turn if he's targeted by an card you can discard the same type of Card (Monster, Spell, Trap) to negate that effect. Unlike Arcana Extra Joker he negates the effect and not the activation which is an important difference. For Example an activation can be negated in Damage Step too. 

Outside of his very formidable ATK Statline there's not much to talk about him. He's the upgraded form of Jack's Knight in terms of lore. 

 

Arcana Triumph Joker is a L10 Maindeck Warrior with ?/2500 Statline. She can be summoned from the Hand or GY by sending all three Musketeers from Hand or Field to the GY. Note that you may also summon her with 2 Tributes. This summon is also not limited to any kind of once per turn. 

She also gains 500 ATK for every Card in both players hands. After using The Revived Sky God she has a devastating 6000 ATK minimum. Get some more Joker cards and draw through Court of Cards and she's almost easily 8000+ ATK strong. 

Finally she can discard a Monster, Spell or Trap to destroy all Face up cards of the same type from the opponent. This also is not a once per turn. All in all she's easily the strongest of the three Arcana Boss Monsters and a recurring Threat not to be underestimated. 

She's the upgraded form of Queen's Knight in terms of lore. Queen's Knight may have been the weakest in the past but her upgraded Form turns out to be the strongest of them all. 

 

The Final Boss which the Deck is centered around is none other then Slifer the Sky Dragon himself. His Normal summon cannot be negated. He gains 1000 ATK/DEF for every card in your Hand and every Monster the opponent summons in Attack position will loose 2000 ATK and will be destroyed if it reaches 0 ATK through this effect. 

Summoning him during the opponents turn can turn every Link based strategy into an Nightmare. With his unique Divine Attribute and Divine Beast typing he has immunity against quite a few cards by nature. 

The one downside is that if he's Special summoned he will be send to the GY during the End Phase of that turn. 

Using the Joker cards Court of Cards and The Revived Sky God will make him reach 10000 ATK and more with ease. Thunderspeed Summon can search and summon him so he's always there to be big trouble for the opponent. 

That's it for the Boss Monster lineup for our Strategy here. Remember that Royal Straight Slasher also exists so if you find some Space for 6 Cards which would be replacing the Slifer cards basically you can consider him too. 

He needs an additional L1, L2 and L3 Monster for his Boardwipe effect which the Archetype does not provide. If you don't mind that, use Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring , Plaguespreader Zombie and Effect Veiler to name some easy choices. Add 2x Royal Straight on top of him and he's ready to be used. 

 

Short comments on additional Spice

The Extra Deck we see here is filled with stuff to strengthen the overall Consistency and Power of this Deck. Idaten the Conqueror Star can be summoned with 2 L5 or higher Warrior Monsters and searches a L5 Warrior Monster on summon. He has some Battle related effects too and is a good Face Card Fusion target if you are missing a way to bring the three Musketeers onto the field. 

So Joker's Straight locks into LIGHT Warrior Extra Deck summons that's why stuff like Constellar Pleiades can be found here. He's just a good guy in every Situation with his universal Bounce effect. 

Same applies for Heroic Champion - Claivesolish who severely strengthens the OTK Potential of this Deck all by himself. A Imperial Bower and Joker's Straight opening is an swift OTK thanks to this card. 

Daigusto Emeral is here to recycle 3 Monsters and Draw a card and you can even use his revival effect to bring back normal Monsters. 

Imperial Princess Quinquery is L5 support and brings out more L5 Monsters easily. Jack's Knight can turn into Joker's Knight thanks to her. 

Lyna the Light Charmer, Lustrous is a slow search option to get Starters or steal opponents LIGHT Monsters. 

And Hip Hoshiningen , Ferocious Flame Swordsman and Defender of the Labyrinth all three give an ATK Boost to your Monsters and have some kind of recycling on top of that. Just the right guy no matter the Situation is the thought behind them. 

 

3 Jack's Knight and a Dream 

As always every Deck has it's weakspots and it's no difference with this one. As the headline might already suggest the potential to Draw a useless Brick Hand in a Deck with 6 vanillas is certainly here. The three Musketeers are essencial to bring the Deck up to speed but also hold it back if you draw 3 of one of them. 

Old Boss Monsters like Arcana Knight Joker are also something every modern Deck can deal with nowadays. The real deal is Arcana Triumph Joker Which is why the whole Fusion Strategy is almost unncessary. I say almost since a card like Idaten the Conqueror Star is very useful to unbrick and even Arcana Knight Joker is still a 3800 ATK Body which is big and threatens OTKs easily. 

With a few of the right cards this Deck can OTK pretty easily but going second you might find yourself unable to do just that since an Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring can crush all your Dreams. On the other Hand Maxx "C" will happily let the opponent Draw cards until he stops smiling the moment a very chonky Arcana Triumph Joker enters the field. 

Going first your best bet is to setup a Slifer interruption in the opponents turn which may just be enough to crush his Strategy alltogether. The Revived Sky God can also set you up for a devastating chain of Boss Monster summons in one turn. I remember once summoning Slifer and all 3 Arcana Bosses in one turn against Swordsoul. That was a great Duel since he didn't surrender and just let it happen. 

In total this Strategy is not perfect like every Deck but it surely is better then your average Egyptian God Deck. You know the ones with Egyptian God Slime and all that The Winged Dragon of Ra focus. 

 

Final Divine Words

I tried my best to keep it short and easy to understand with this Deck profile. This Deck turns out to be a Yugi classic which actually works like a well rounded Strategy. It's also a very fun Deck which you don't see to much in Master Duels High Ranks. 

As mentioned sometimes already now you can also delete the Slifer Focus and instead use Royal Straight Slasher or you are crazy and use both (Bricks like... but with enough outside support it may work). Slifer will always be my favourite of the egyptian gods and I'm glad he found his home in this Musketeer Strategy.

If you like Slifer, Poker Cards or Yugi in general and want to play a fun Deck try it, you won't regret it^^ It's also quite the good one since you can aim for Platinum League and higher with this one easily. 

 

Final Rating: 

★★★★★★★ OTK Potential

★★★☆☆☆☆ Defensive Tools

★★★★☆☆☆ Control Options

★★★★★☆☆ Removal Options

★★★★★★★ Recovery/Recycling

★★★★★★★ Card Advantage

Overall Rating: ★★★★★☆☆  33/42★

 

 

Poker Master Rules

Like always there's a few cards with some less obvious rules which I'm gonna talk about here. 

Slifer the Sky Dragon: His ATK reduction effect only triggers if a Monster is summoned in Attack Position. 

Arcana Triumph Joker: Unlike many modern cards this card has no once per turn limitations. 

Joker's Knight: Milling a Musketeer from Deck is a Cost to summon him from the Hand. 

Face Card Fusion: Unlike with other cards in this Archetype you only need to control one Musketeer to use the additional effect of this card. 

Joker's Wild: This card can copy the whole effect of the 4 Spell cards which have the three Musketeers in it's name. These Spell cards do not come with costs so after activating this card you resolve the milled Spell card just like how it's written on the Spell Card but as the effect of Joker's Wild. 

Arcana Extra Joker: He can prevent targeting from opponents Monster who he points to as well.

deck_excerpt: Relay Soul Win ft. Jinzo + Crackdown
deck_description:
Hey, how you doing? About a month ago, I have won with Relay Soul and decided to do it again with a different setup: A dancer Jinzo, who would have thought :D

 

 

Gameplan

1) Discard Banisher with Ravenous. Then, place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon with its ability to unlock "Primal Seed" loop. As long as you don't banish Ancient/Banisher with Chaos Emperor by accident, all is well.

2) Destroy Saryuja with "Offerings to the Doomed" and clear at least 3 x Main Monster Zones (MMZ), which will be utilized for Trishula. Then, revive Ancient + Level 1 Tuner + Level 1 Non-Tuner and Synchro Summon Trishula with those three.

3) Activate Trishula to deplete your opponent's resources by banishing anything from their hand + GY + field, which is extremely beneficial if you go second. Repeat this procedure with "De-Synchro" until there is nothing your opponent has.

4) Revive materials of Trishula and tribute them for Plasma. Then, revive Ancient + Martial/Shamisen with "Monster Reborn" and Synchro Summon Baronne. Place it on Extra Monster Zone (EMZ).

5) Revive Cthugua + Martial/Shamisen with "Monster Reborn" but before you Synchro Summon Salamander with said monsters, play "Pot of Avarice" once by targeting 5 x Main Deck monsters. Then, give your opponent Jinzo + Relay Soul with "Gold Moon Coin" and set Primal Seed + Drop Off + Crackdown. Finally, you can bring forth Salamander to not deck out easily.

6) Revive "Banisher" with "Monster Reborn" and destroy ME-PSY-YA with Baronne. Now, everything will be banished instead of just Spell/Trap cards. End your turn but don't forget to set "Primal Seed" as well.

7) On your opponent's Draw Phase, activate "Drop Off". If needed, negate whatever your opponent can activate with Baronne in response to "Drop Off", just in case.

8) If your opponent sets "Relay Soul", here is how to win:

  • Your opponent concedes, which can happen most of the time even before all of that, especially while depleting your opponent's resources with Trishula done in #3.
  • Your opponent doesn't use anything given to them. In that case, attack directly for the win. Also, repeat using Drop Off, which was explained in #7. You can also revive a monster with Reborn and destroy it with Offerings to not draw any cards, although there is no need to thanks to Salamander refilling your deck, done in #5.
  • Your opponent activates "Relay Soul" and Special Summons Jinzo. Rather than being lame and destroying Jinzo with Offerings/Baronne, activate "Crackdown" on Jinzo for coolness factor. Let me explain why...
    1. Jinzo has the ability of negating Trap cards and you can't activate Trap cards.
    2. However, Plasma was here before Jinzo, which can be able to negate opponent's monster effects. One-sided Skill Drain, in a nutshell.
    3. Jinzo can't negate "Crackdown" while under being negated by Plasma. So, "Crackdown" can steal Jinzo, even though it shouldn't.
    4. Jinzo is on your side, meaning the negation effect coming from Plasma has been lifted. However, now Jinzo can negate "Crackdown", so it can be passed to the opponent automatically.
    5. What was explained in #3 and #4 is going to happen back and forth, while Jinzo is switching sides. Since this loop is infinite, game decides to find the culprit and end this madness by killing it, which is "Jinzo".

9) Congratulations, you have won with Relay Soul!

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contact Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Monster Reborn" is given for free, if you have completed the tutorial to save 30 UR!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 60 SR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Lavalval Salamander" can be found within "Combatants of Flame" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Trishula, Dragon of the Ice Barrier" can be found within "Glacial Seal" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Destiny HERO - Plasma" can be found within "Shrouded Heroes" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Baronne de Fleur" can be found within "The Noble Knights of Crimson Flowers" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Moray of Avarice" can be found within "Treasures of the Cosmic Ocean" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Ravenous" + "Pot of Acquisitiveness" + "Jinzo" + "Relay Soul" + "Drop Off" + "Primal Seed" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 150 SR and 60 UR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 600 SR and 270 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. Let me know if you have any questions and have fun in Master Duel!

deck_excerpt: Ptolemaeus Turn Skip Win ft. Daidarant + Overlay Regen + Whiptail
deck_description:
Hello there! You got Ptolemaeus laying around but figuring out how to win without going pure Tellarknights? In this Panda deck, we will prove that how, so keep reading.

 

 

Gameplan

1) XYZ Summon Daidarant and activate its monster ability to place it on Pendulum Zone. Then, place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon by banishing Integrator + Level 1 dude to activate "Primal Seed" loop.

2) XYZ Summon Ptolemaeus, right behind any Extra Monster Zones (EMZ), with Panda + Monk but don't include Cthuguas to not deck out by accident. Then, Link Summon Reprodocus by using any two monsters but Ptolemaeus + Chaos Emperor as materials, right above where Ptolemaeus is.

3) To skip your opponent's turn, you have to detach exactly 7 materials from Ptolemaeus. Fortunately, you can get exactly 7 materials as explained below...

  • First, attach 3 x Overlay Regen from your hand.
  • Second, activate Daidarant from Pendulum Zone to attach it from the field.
  • Third, activate Reprodocus and change the Type of Ptolemaeus as Beast-Warrior to attach 3 x Zoodiac Whiptail from your hand.
  • Finally, detach 3 x Overlay Regen + Daidarant + 3 x Whiptail. Therefore, 7 materials were detached and your opponent's turn has been skipped.

4) You can also repeat what was explained in #3, in case DPS is low...

  • First, fetch "Overlay Regen" cards from Banish Zone (BZ) to your hand with "Primal Seed" loop. There, you can attach them from your hand.
  • Second, revive Daidarant with "Monster Reborn" and destroy it with "Offerings to the Doomed", which lets you place it into Pendulum Zone. Thus, you can attach it from the field but know that it has hard once per turn and you have to do what I told you on next turn. This step also lets you to not deck out because Offerings skips your next Draw Phase, if used at least once.
  • Third, repeat the same Type change with Reprodocus and revive 3 x Whiptail with "Monster Reborn", where you can also attach Whiptails from your field.
  • Finally, detach 3 x Overlay Regen + Daidarant + 3 x Whiptail. Therefore, 7 materials were detached and your opponent's turn has been skipped.

5) Revive monsters which have high amount of DPS. Then, bash your opponent up while repeating what was explained in #3 and #4, until your opponent is dead.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Monster Reborn" is given for free, if you have completed the tutorial to save 30 UR!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Ravenous" + "Pot of Acquisitiveness" + "Primal Seed" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 60 SR and 60 UR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 480 SR and 180 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. Let me know if you have any questions and have fun in Master Duel!

For a friend to learn yugioh.

Explanations of this deck :


Main Deck (engine) :

3x - Sky Striker Ace - Raye : There is no sky striker deck if it has less than 3 copies of Raye.

0x - Sky Striker Ace - Roze : In the past, before sky cards started to leave the list, such as engage and multirole, your sky strike gameplay was around your starting hand coming with a card that guaranteed you to create a sky striker link, which are the cards roze, raye, engage, rota, hornet drones, or the combination of the field together with an mst or multirole. So, so you don't depend on a combination of two cards, field and mst/multirole, it was advantageous to put roze to have a greater chance of being able to start playing... However, with the return of engage and multirole, let's go back to playing like we used to. , of course roze adds new moves, but I don't think it's worth the price, I think it's an unnecessary, slow, heavy card...

3x - Sky Striker Mobilize - Engage! : Probably the strongest card in the deck, so as many copies of it as possible, it will probably come off the list, so in the future swap the upstart goblin for another copy of engage.

3x - Sky Striker Mobilize - Linkage! : This letter is very good, without a doubt 3 copies of it should be included.

1º - This card protects you from effects that target your monster.

2º - This card allows you to make plays that only forbidden droplet would do, which is to play a card from the capo to the gy as a cost, so if you have 2 magic cards in your gy and activate engage(chain link 1) and then activate linkage(chain link 2), you can play engage as a cost in gy, then when the effects resolve, you will summon kagari, and when engage resolves the effect she will draw +1 card, when the effects resolve to Kagari will be activated and you will get engage, activating engage again and being able to draw +1 card in the process.
3º - It used to be a danger to place a non-sky striker monster in your extra monster zone, now you can easily remove it and replace a sky striker link.

3x - Sky Striker Airspace - Area Zero : As you are using many sky striker cards, it obviously deserves to have 3 copies, in addition to being destroyed by multirole.

3x - Sky Striker Mecha - Widow Anchor : Most decks have monsters that activate effects on the field, so 3 copies is ideal.

3x - Sky Striker Mecha - Eagle Booster : As the use of hand traps has become popular, eagle booster is essential to defend yourself.

2x - Sky Striker Mecha - Shark Cannon : It has a reduced number, as not all decks activate cards within the gy.

2x - Sky Striker Maneuver - Afterburners! : Also has a reduced number, as it is a normal spell.

1x - Sky Striker Mecha - Hornet Drones : It serves as a Raye...

1x - ROTA : It serves as a Raye...

1x - Terraforming - It serves as a Area Zero...

_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Main Deck (tech cards) :

3x - Ash Blossom : Probably the hand trap that works in all decks.

9x - Hand Traps : As the sky striker's choice will almost always be to go second, so the tech card choices will be hand traps, there is the possibility of using cards that break fields, however in sky I don't think it will be very useful, since the sky striker it takes a few turns to actually start playing, unlike other decks that use cards that break the field, these decks can break the enemy field and end the game, something that sky striker cannot do, so ideally you focus on taking cards from your opponent in the process of creating his field, and not letting him make the field and then try to break it.

#########################################################################################################

Extra Deck :
 
3x - Sky Striker Ace - Shizuku : She is a good card.

3x - Sky Striker Ace - Kagari : Your strongest extra deck card.

2x - Sky Striker Ace - Hayate : Just 2 hayate, as the games are not lasting long, if we go to a meta with the game lasting longer, then yes it makes sense to use 3 hayate.

1x - Sky Striker Ace - Kaina : It helps you not to die... its link arrow is really cool, as it points to your field, like Hayate's arrow, so you can place 2 link sky strikers in your field using linkage, without having to spend a copy of Hayate.

1x - Sky Striker Ace - Zeke : This card is a good card, especially when it is to summon a higher link, as just use its effect on the field and summon another Raye, thus being able to make the unicorn, together with its first effect you will take away 2 monsters from your opponent, but remember that the effect of banishing a monster from it does not solve the problem, but rather postpones it. For these reasons she is superior to Azalea, and to use Azalea it will be more useful to include Roze, but as already mentioned, Roze is not a good card.

1x - S:P Little Knight : This card is fantastic in Sky Striker, it is a thousand times improved version of Knightmare Phoenix. It is used to deal with floodgates and unwanted monsters.

1x - Hiita The Fire Charmer, Ablaze : This card serves as a ladder for your larger links, but it is also extremely useful in mirror matches, as you can use it to bring a Kagari from the opente without having to use yours.

1x - Knightmare Unicorn : This card a field removal, without having to destroy.
 
1x - Ningirsu The World Chalice Warrior : This card a field removal, his big difference is that he doesn't give targets.

1x - Topologic Bomber Dragon : Sky striker is not a good deck to deal with a field full of monsters, that's why it is in the deck, in addition to giving multiple raigekis, it is your match finisher, combine it with hornet drones, eagle booster and multirole, gg. I don't like Accesscode Talker, I think it takes away from the premise of the deck, when I see someone sweating Accesscode Talker seems to me like someone who doesn't understand the mechanics of the deck, and wants to win on the second turn, but sky striker is not a salamangreat that can do this, the sky striker is the sky striker... deal with it.

#########################################################################################################

Extra Deck :

3x - Fobidden Droplet : This is one of the best cards to use in a sky striker's side deck, it is excellent for playing against monsters that cannot target, for this reason and the great possibility of plays that can be made with this card, I would always keep this card in my sides decks regardless of the meta.

3x - Shared Hide : This card is another card that I would never take out of the side deck regardless of the meta, this card is exceptional against the mirror match, and today practically all decks draw a lot of cards.

9x - Rest of the side deck : Meta game analysis.

Hey, are you a Blue-Eyes fan? If you are, I would like to show you how to FTK with Deep-Eyes alongside "Treasure Panda". Let's jump in!

 

 

Gameplan

1) Play "Temple >>> Rebirth" combo and choose Dragon as Type. Also, use "Raigeki" to make two adjacent columns of your opponent's side free, if you must.

2) Special Summon Yajiro with Saryuja and place Yajiro to the center of the battlefield or it will detonate itself. Then, give Yajiro to your opponent with "Shien's Spy".

3) Change the button on the lower right corner of the screen to either "ON" or "Auto" to not miss anything. Then, activate "Vision with Eyes of Blue" away from Yajiro. When asked at first, reveal Blue-Eyes and Special Summon Blue-Eyes within Yajiro's sight to let Blue-Eyes be destroyed by Yajiro.

4) Thanks to Yajiro, activate Deep-Eyes from hand to Special Summon it opposite to Yajiro and deal tons of damage. Even though we didn't have lots of Dragon monsters by default, "Rebirth Judgment" changed this outcome in that regard to favor Deep-Eyes.

5) Use "Vision with Eyes of Blue" again. This time, return Deep-Eyes to hand and Special Summon Blue-Eyes to field. Place Blue-Eyes where Yajiro is able to destroy Blue-Eyes.

6) Repeat what was done in #4 and victory is yours!

deck_excerpt: Wake Up Your Elemental HERO OTK ft. Arcana + Rebirth Judgment
deck_description:
Greetings! In this deck, you are going to overkill your opponent. If you want to punch your opponent as many times as you want, here is how...

 

Gameplan

1) Fill your opponent's board with flowers thanks to "Black Garden".

2) Place "Light Barrier" and Special Summon Arcana with Saryuja. Choose the outcome as heads to always skip your opponent's turn at the cost of sending two of your monsters to GY, which will be Arcana + Saryuja.

3) If you have played "Into the Void" and keeping most if not all monsters in-hand, especially Wildheart + Bladedge, end your turn but not before setting 2 x Miracle Fusion + Rebirth Judgment. Send Arcana + Saryuja to GY and skip your opponent's turn.

4) It's your turn now. First, activate "Rebirth Judgment" to change the Type of monsters in your GY as Warrior. Next, play "Miracle Fusion" to bring forth Wildedge by banishing Wildheart + Bladedge from your GY as materials. Then, play "Miracle Fusion" another time to bring forth "Wake Up" by banishing Wildedge from your field and as many Warrior monsters as there are in your GY as materials.

5) Even though there aren't lots of Warrior monsters in your GY by default, thanks to "Rebirth Judgment", you have banished lots of monsters and "Wake Up" can attack a bunch of times each Battle Phase to kill your opponent for sure. In case of Evenly Matched and alike, I hope you have Baronne present to negate it.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Rebirth Judgment" can be collected by purchasing "Cybernetic Successor" deck. 30 UR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Arcana Force XXI - The World" + "Light Barrier" can be found within "Hand of Fate" Secret Pack to save 30 SR and 30 UR!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 60 SR!

- "Black Garden" can be found within "Exquisite Jet-Black Rose" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Baronne de Fleur" can be found within "The Noble Knights of Crimson Flowers" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Moray of Avarice" can be found within "Treasures of the Cosmic Ocean" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Ravenous" + "Pot of Acquisitiveness" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 60 SR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 570 SR and 150 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. Let me know if you have any questions and have fun in Master Duel!

The Little Ghost's that could

This deck is aimed toward getting Psychic Rover on the field as soon as possible and loop his effect.

Emergency Teleport, Dice Dungeon into Dimension Dice can do that. Foolish Burial can send Rover to GY, as can Spright Sprind sending from the deck, or Gigantic Spright can summon him from deck.

Power Well is a Quick Effect Monster Reborn for ALL Rovers on your GY so their effects start popping off.
Spright Elf can revive Rover as Quick Effect once per turn.
If you summon Rover to an arrow that Topologic Bomber Dragon points to, like with Power Well on opponent's turn, he will destroy all monsters in the main monster zone. This is NOT A ONCE PER TURN. Which makes him and Rover a looping monster wipe.

Spright Pixies is here both as an extra special summon for the plays AND as a battle handtrap to make your Rovers able to crash against people.

Shadowpriestess is the FTK tool here, if you get her and Rover on the field she can keep tributing rover for 800 every time. If Rover fails to come to the field you can fish him back with any of the cards mentioned above and keep going again. Selene Link is here to get Shadowpriestess back from GY, be it from destruction or because of Reasoning and others.

Have fun and best of luck on Rover's effect!!
